      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>In step 8 of fatty-acid biosynthesis (Figure 29.6), reduction of <i>trans</i>-crotonyl ACP gives butyryl ACP. A hydride from NADPH adds to C3 of the crotonyl group from the Re face, and protonation on C2 occurs on the Si face. Is the reduction a syn addition or an anti addition?</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBdkFaIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--95637528531668abdb38949772dcac9709f10e91/OChem_29_EC_021.jpg\" alt=\"trans-Crotonyl ACP reacts to form butyryl A C P. The product has a four-carbon chain with carbonyl linked to S A C P.\">",
